President Obama spoke with Greek Prime Minister Antonis Samaras to congratulate him on his election and the formation of his coalition government. The President expressed his strong support for Greece and emphasized the solidarity between the American and Greek people. He also encouraged Prime Minister Samaras to work closely with the European Union, the International Monetary Fund, and the European Central Bank to address Greece's economic situation and implement its reform program. Additionally, President Obama wished the Prime Minister a speedy recovery from his recent eye surgery.